Create Volume
      ↓
docker volume create volume-v1

Run Container + Attach Volume
      ↓
docker run -dit --name cont-1 -v volume-v1:/app nginx
------------------------------------
docker run -dit --name cont-1 -v volume-v1:/app nginx
Meaning

cont-1 → container name

volume-v1 → Docker volume

/app → folder inside container

nginx → container image (from Nginx)

📦 Now the volume is attached to /app inside the container.
